  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis index for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5, supporting a regulatory submission decision. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all 13 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels under the Minimal profile review. Decision: Accepted for the stated intended use of predicting hemolysis trends for comparative device evaluation in VAD therapy.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-cfd-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/hemolysis-index-bench-measurements"
  ],
